</style></head><body class="c9"><h1 class="c1 c10" id="h.sz5r2bs4m63f"><span>The Tic-Tac-Toe Challenge</span></h1><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1 c15"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.sz5r2bs4m63f" target="_blank">The Tic-Tac-Toe Challenge</a></span></p><p class="c1 c17"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.wxloo0h0m0aj" target="_blank">About the challenge</a></span></p><p class="c1 c13"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.2g9c3mjgu2fq" target="_blank">What won&amp;rsquo;t change</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.bbjwmaucik3n" target="_blank">What will change</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.9a6iks7do4d9" target="_blank">The Challenge</a></span></p><p class="c1 c4"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.1h2tsoeaafnw" target="_blank">Scoring</a></span></p><p class="c17 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.f2tvldv7nvpr" target="_blank">The 3x3 Tic-Tac-Toe Specification</a></span></p><p class="c4 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.f4z1w1zg4jap" target="_blank">What this specification doesn&amp;rsquo;t say&amp;hellip;</a></span></p><p class="c4 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.h934fbh4ghw6" target="_blank">What this specification says&amp;hellip;</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.8tsmal8j741m" target="_blank">The Board &amp;nbsp;(Edit cell list)</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.ite44ly8203r" target="_blank">The Players &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(Edit)</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.nqyznvviywm6" target="_blank">Cell Translations &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(Edit)</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.klnut67sluwp" target="_blank">Cell Patterns &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(Edit)</a></span></p><p class="c13 c1 c18"><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#h.qigc2qfmnlun" target="_blank">Target Platforms &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; (Edit)</a></span></p><p class="c1"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span><span class="c16">&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/Codee42/StartBuild?projectName=TicTacToe&amp;scriptName=Cook&amp;returnUrl=/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/ReadMe.html">Quick Build</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;- Chameleon Code SDK</span></p><h2 class="c1 c10" id="h.wxloo0h0m0aj"><span>About the challenge</span></h2><p class="c1"><span>This website serves as a highly detailed specification for a game of Tic-Tac-Toe (</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/TargetPlatforms.html" target="_blank">example</a></span><span>). &amp;nbsp;Every detail of </span><span class="c6">what </span><span>the game should be, and </span><span class="c6">what </span><span>it should do has been described, from the </span><span class="c0 c11"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/TheBoard.html" target="_blank">board</a></span><span class="c11">, </span><span class="c0 c11"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/PlayerLevels.html" target="_blank">players</a></span><span class="c11">, </span><span class="c0 c11"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/CellPatterns.html" target="_blank">cells</a></span><span class="c11">, </span><span class="c0 c11"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/Player_Intermediate.html" target="_blank">strategies</a></span><span class="c11">, etc</span><span>. &amp;nbsp;What has </span><span class="c11">not </span><span>been detailed is </span><span class="c6">how</span><span>&amp;nbsp;the game should be created.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.2g9c3mjgu2fq"><span>What won&amp;rsquo;t change</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>There is only 1 constant, which will never change - this is a </span><span class="c6">3x3, traditional tic-tac-toe game</span><span>. &amp;nbsp;This is not </span><span class="c6">Connect 4</span><span>&amp;nbsp;or </span><span class="c6">Connect N</span><span>. &amp;nbsp;3x3 Tic-Tac-Toe is the sandbox we&amp;rsquo;re playing in. &amp;nbsp;Other than that, pretty much everything&amp;rsquo;s up for grabs.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.bbjwmaucik3n"><span>What will change</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>The </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=1934124403" target="_blank">GSheet</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;which defines this specification includes two different types of cells - white and gray. &amp;nbsp;All white cells are subject to change, at any time, gray cells are not expected to change.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><ul class="c12 lst-kix_jlrry974geqe-0 start"><li class="c2 c1"><span class="c6">White Cells:</span><span>&amp;nbsp;If only values with a white background are changed, and your solution requires hand code changes in response, points will be subtracted.<br /></span></li><li class="c2 c1"><span class="c6">Gray Cells:</span><span>&amp;nbsp; If values with a gray background change, and no hand code changes are required to comply, additional points may be awarded to your solutions - because, hand code changes are expected if gray background values change.</span></li></ul><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.9a6iks7do4d9"><span>The Challenge</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>Implement this specification in the language, platform and environment of your choice. &amp;nbsp;Use whatever tools you want.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><h3 class="c1 c10" id="h.1h2tsoeaafnw"><span>Scoring</span></h3><p class="c1"><span>Solutions </span><span>will be scored by first accumulating points based on how many of the features in the specification are implemented, with subtractions for any deviations from &amp;ldquo;the spec&amp;rdquo;, &amp;nbsp;as well as subtractions for each additional hour of time invested. </span></p><h2 class="c1 c10" id="h.f2tvldv7nvpr"><span>The 3x3 Tic-Tac-Toe Specification</span></h2><p class="c1"><span>TicTacToe is a game that is simple enough that once you learn how to play it, you can either tie or win every game. &amp;nbsp;The only way to lose (once you know how) is to make a mistake.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1"><span>This makes it a well suited problem for an entry level programming exercise. &amp;nbsp;This documentation is broken up into a few different parts. &amp;nbsp;Explore the Additional Resources for a complete list, but at a high level it works like this.</span></p><h3 class="c1 c10" id="h.f4z1w1zg4jap"><span>What this specification doesn&amp;rsquo;t say&amp;hellip;</span></h3><p class="c1"><span>This specification makes no mention of any of the following:</span></p><ul class="c12 lst-kix_w2m1p1bhc071-0 start"><li class="c2 c1"><span>The &amp;ldquo;kind&amp;rdquo; of app? (web, android, ios, console, windows, linux, etc, etc)</span></li><li class="c2 c1"><span>Which language should be used? (Python, Java, JavaScript, CSharp, etc, etc)</span></li><li class="c1 c2"><span>Patterns followed (Procedural, Object Oriented, Functional, etc, etc)</span></li><li class="c2 c1"><span>How to actually implement any of the strategies discussed.<br /></span></li></ul><p class="c1"><span>Really - there is virtually no discussion of </span><span class="c6">how</span><span>&amp;nbsp;at all. &amp;nbsp;It only contains the &amp;ldquo;axiomatic agreements&amp;rdquo;, the &amp;ldquo;facts&amp;rdquo;... or &amp;ldquo;answers to the &amp;lsquo;what&amp;rsquo; questions&amp;rdquo;. &amp;nbsp;For example, <br /></span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span class="c6">QUESTION:</span><span><br />If we assign (from the top left of the board) an index of 0..8 of each cell, </span><span class="c6">what</span><span>&amp;nbsp;are the indexes which replace these for a 90 degree CLOCKWISE rotation around the middle cell?</span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span><br /></span><span class="c6">ANSWER</span><span>: &amp;nbsp;630741852</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1"><span>This is simply a fact which is true regardless of language, platform, implementation detail, etc. &amp;nbsp;In pseudo code, a unit test for an implementation might look like this:<br /></span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span class="c5">TicTacToeBoard b = new()</span></p><p class="c1 c7 c14"><span class="c5"></span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span class="c5">b.SetCells(012345678) </span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span class="c5">b.Rotate()</span></p><p class="c1 c14 c7"><span class="c5"></span></p><p class="c1 c14"><span class="c5">Assert: b.CellOrder() == 630741852<br /></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c6">How </span><span>to rotate the cells is entirely up to each implementation. &amp;nbsp;The resulting order is non-negotiable however.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1"><span>So this &amp;ldquo;specification&amp;rdquo; documents what the result should be - not how to get there. &amp;nbsp;What will change? &amp;nbsp;The different levels of players, ever word, color, symbol that shows up in the UI, strategies, patterns, translations. &amp;nbsp;All of it is subject to change, at any time. &amp;nbsp;Expect more. &amp;nbsp;</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c6">For example:</span><span><br />To start with there are Rotate and Flip translations, but the pattern easily allows for us to add an AntiFlip and an AnitRotate which would rotate and flip &amp;ldquo;the other way&amp;rdquo; around.</span></p><h3 class="c1 c10" id="h.h934fbh4ghw6"><span>What this specification says&amp;hellip;</span></h3><p class="c1"><span>This specification describes what your solution needs to do. &amp;nbsp;It does not describe how to do it. &amp;nbsp;The specification details are split up into the following primary areas of interest.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.8tsmal8j741m"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px;"><img alt="" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/KkfXqhBpZP-pz0_s4KjhOGGmXYkFd6tWjL8SLdQ9BtiQBd2InwoDH-hFFf4d33w2eNozFoGQM9afuaT0C1VOM25DVPGxMFvIRhKAOY_FwMuuk3HgXQ0Vj5jUG9hfYgf9dA" style="width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);" title="" /></span><span class="c0 c6"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/TheBoard.html">The Board</a></span><span class="c6">&amp;nbsp; </span><span class="c0 c8"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=1934124403" target="_blank">(Edit cell list</a></span><span class="c8">)</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>This </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/TheBoard.html">Detailed analysis of The board</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;is made up of </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_Cells.html">nine cells</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;(</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=1934124403" target="_blank">edit</a></span><span>). &amp;nbsp;Each cell has a position, index and one of three </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_CellStates.html">cell states</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;(</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=194238261" target="_blank">edit</a></span><span>). &amp;nbsp;The additional information about each cell includes information like an index per cell, and an index for that cell if it were rotated or flipped.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.ite44ly8203r"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px;"><img alt="" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/KkfXqhBpZP-pz0_s4KjhOGGmXYkFd6tWjL8SLdQ9BtiQBd2InwoDH-hFFf4d33w2eNozFoGQM9afuaT0C1VOM25DVPGxMFvIRhKAOY_FwMuuk3HgXQ0Vj5jUG9hfYgf9dA" style="width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);" title="" /></span><span class="c0 c6"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/PlayerLevels.html">The Players</a></span><span class="c6">&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; </span><span class="c8">(</span><span class="c0 c8"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=260512170" target="_blank">Edit</a></span><span class="c8">)</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>There are different kinds of Players (or </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_AILevels.html">Player Levels</a></span><span>) and the </span><span class="c6">Player Level </span><span>indicates which (if any) of the </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_AIStrategies.html">AI Strategies</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;will be used. &amp;nbsp;See a </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/PlayerLevels.html">detailed analysis of these player levels</a></span><span>.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.nqyznvviywm6"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px;"><img alt="" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/KkfXqhBpZP-pz0_s4KjhOGGmXYkFd6tWjL8SLdQ9BtiQBd2InwoDH-hFFf4d33w2eNozFoGQM9afuaT0C1VOM25DVPGxMFvIRhKAOY_FwMuuk3HgXQ0Vj5jUG9hfYgf9dA" style="width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);" title="" /></span><span class="c0 c6"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/Translations.html">Cell Translations</a></span><span class="c6">&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; </span><span class="c8">(</span><span class="c0 c8"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=1319606678" target="_blank">Edit</a></span><span class="c8">)</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>View 1st </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_TranslationTests.html">Translation Testing</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;Json - </span><span>Using this flip/rotate index data, the following </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_TranslationTests.html">translation test data</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;can be used to validate values..</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.klnut67sluwp"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px;"><img alt="" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/KkfXqhBpZP-pz0_s4KjhOGGmXYkFd6tWjL8SLdQ9BtiQBd2InwoDH-hFFf4d33w2eNozFoGQM9afuaT0C1VOM25DVPGxMFvIRhKAOY_FwMuuk3HgXQ0Vj5jUG9hfYgf9dA" style="width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);" title="" /></span><span class="c0 c6"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/CellPatterns.html">Cell Patterns</a></span><span class="c6">&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; </span><span class="c8">(</span><span class="c0 c8"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=412235242" target="_blank">Edit</a></span><span class="c8">)</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>Many of the strategies use these </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/$SDK_ROOT_URI$/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_CellPatterns.html">patterns </a></span><span>(</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=412235242" target="_blank">edit</a></span><span>). &amp;nbsp;These patterns use translations to limit the number of patterns which must be represented. &amp;nbsp;These translations are </span><span class="c6">Rotate</span><span>&amp;nbsp;and </span><span class="c6">Flip</span><span>&amp;nbsp;they are described in more details in the </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/AdditionalResources/Resource_Translations.html">translation list</a></span><span>&amp;nbsp;(</span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=1319606678" target="_blank">edit</a></span><span>).</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1"><span>The patterns are all expressed as a sequence of &amp;nbsp;</span><span class="c6">##;##;##;... &amp;nbsp;<br /><br /></span><span>where the first # is the </span><span class="c6">CellIndex </span><span>and the second # is the </span><span class="c6">CellState Id</span><span>, always followed by a semi-colon.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1"><span>The </span><span class="c6">Translations</span><span>&amp;nbsp;is a similar format, but the ##&amp;rsquo;s refer to the number of translations, followed by which translation to use.</span></p><h4 class="c1 c10" id="h.qigc2qfmnlun"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px;"><img alt="" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/KkfXqhBpZP-pz0_s4KjhOGGmXYkFd6tWjL8SLdQ9BtiQBd2InwoDH-hFFf4d33w2eNozFoGQM9afuaT0C1VOM25DVPGxMFvIRhKAOY_FwMuuk3HgXQ0Vj5jUG9hfYgf9dA" style="width: 31.50px; height: 31.50px; margin-left: 0.00px; margin-top: 0.00px; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px);" title="" /></span><span class="c0 c6"><a class="c3" href="https://eejai42.sdks.codeiverse.com/TicTacToeSDK/Docs/TargetPlatforms.html" target="_blank">Target Platforms</a></span><span class="c6">&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;</span><span class="c8">(</span><span class="c0 c8"><a class="c3" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1xpLGHj6wHyot9Kp2lpKTG8AcKJNMSkxjp-aTQT7yB90/edit#gid=2077194606" target="_blank">Edit</a></span><span class="c8">)</span></h4><p class="c1"><span>This game is specified in such a way that it can be implemented on many different platforms. &amp;nbsp;The goal however, is to have as much as possible come from this specification - shared across all the platforms. &amp;nbsp;This way, when the specification changes, the code changes - across all the platforms.<br /><br />This challenge is essentially about adding your solution to this list of target platforms which implement this specification.</span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p><p class="c1 c7"><span></span></p></body></html>